The Folweni police station, south of Durban, stands empty for now, after it was revealed that a police officer had tested positive for the coronavirus (Covid-19) Police spokesperson Brig Vishnu Naidoo confirmed in a media report that as a precautionary measure, health officials had evacuated members at the Folweni police station for the purpose of sanitisation. Brig Naidoo said, “A member who was feeling unwell was admitted to St Augustine’s Hospital and tested positive for Covid-19.  Naidoo said the station is not shut down as the services have been moved to a mobile operation and all Covid-19 protocols are being implemented. “It is important to note that no other members have shown any symptoms or high fever. Anyone who has come into close contact with the member who tested positive is currently in self-isolation.”